AGI - Continue to rain in Spain>, causing a lot of damage. This time the disturbance "Laurence" > touched the south of the peninsula where a woman died in Seville and still seeks her husband.&nbsp; The vehicle of the couple “turned and was overwhelmed by the current” in Constantina, a village about 85 km north-east of Seville, explained a spokesman of the Consorcio of the province, which groups different institutions of the region.
Today 19 water courses in the region were at a red level > 14 of which in the Guadalquivir basin because of the high level of water, which led people to be saved by helicopter. The paratories of the largest river of Andalusia, which passes through Seville, were closed by decision of the Municipality >, which raised the emergency plan at level 1 due to the rise of water.
It is also lost a cyclist released on Monday in Añora (Córdoba). Due to the rain, lessons were also suspended in a dozen schools in Malaga, the closure of numerous roads, including the Sevilla-Cadice highway, > whose lane towards the Andalusian capital was reopened to traffic in the late afternoon, and three railway lines remain interrupted. The showers also caused inconvenience in the Murcia region, where a bus that transported Imserso travelers overturned on the A-7 at the height of Cabezo de Torres, wounding at least 16 people, many of whom in a serious way, while nine people had to be saved after being trapped in two vehicles at Águilas.
Several provinces of the south, southeast, east and center of Spain were put in orange alert Tuesday because of rain, winds and strong tides, on the second day of Laurence's passage to Spain.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> From Thursday a new weather worsening
From Thursday a new storm will come >“with widespread rains and intense winds”, warned the National Weather Agency (Aemet) in a communiqué.
In the region of Murcia>, “nine people trapped in their vehicles” were found healthy and safe from rescue services in the city of Aguilas, reported local emergency services.
For the second consecutive day, the rain interrupted road and rail traffic and increased the flow of rivers, already very heavy after almost three weeks of rain practically uninterrupted throughout Spain.
The last weeks of rain in Spain are about to end the grave drought that struck the country between 2021 and 2024.
